  "description": "This dataset comprises stereoelectroencephalography (sEEG) recordings from patients performing a forced two-choice response task, collected in the epilepsy monitoring unit at Oregon Health & Science University. The data extends characterization of movement-related neural oscillations using intracranial electrode recordings and provides a resource for investigating decision-making and motor control mechanisms at the mesoscale level of brain organization.",
  "methods_description": "Stereoelectroencephalography data were collected from patients in the epilepsy monitoring unit during performance of a forced two-choice response task. Data organization follows the Brain Imaging Data Structure (BIDS) specification for intracranial electrophysiology.",
